Rachel Guttman and Ben Roif at Apartment 3 Pizza combined their passions for pizza making and volunteering to fight food insecurity during the  darkest days of the pandemic.

@apartment3pizza, a pizza pop-up that donates all proceeds to Brooklyn-based hunger relief organizations, was born from their desire to help out. So far, they’ve raised $5,000 and continue using their love of pizza to raise funds for vital charities. 

Know of someone using their passions for good? Nominate them for our Slice of Kindness competition through the link in bio until August 23rd, and they may win a complete Ooni pizza setup.
